        <h1>How to Setup an Attack Server</h1>
        <p>
            Setting up an attack server is often times crucial. Especially in XSS Challenges where we are provided with 
            an admin bot. There are many ways to do this but we will show you a free and easy way to create a temporary
            attack server to use in CTFs Competitions. 
        </p><br>
        <p>
            In this tutorial, we'll be using Pinngy to create a TCP tunnel to give our local web server a public ip
            that can be connected from anywhere in the world. There are many free tunneling services but the one 
            we'll be using is Pinggy as the TCP tunnel is free without need a Credit Card information (unlike ngrok)
        </p>
        
